Text: You will be presented with a series of images. It is your job to learn, through trial and error, whether the “Left” or “Right” arrow key should be pressed for each image.
For some images you should always press “Left”, and for others you should always press “Right” arrow key.
Some images are special: the correct response is the opposite of the preceding correct response.
That is, if the previous correct answer was “Left” then the correct response would now be “Right”.
After each response, you will be told whether you got the item correct or incorrect.
You can take as long as you like on each image, but the task will not continue until you press the “Left” or “Right” arrow key.
The experiment will have three blocks, each block will take approximately 10 minutes to complete.
